{{Infobox power station | name = Blood Hill wind farm | image = Blood Hill Wind Farm.jpg | image_caption = Blood Hill Wind Turbines | location_map = England | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|52|42|43|N|1|40|1|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | name_official = | country = [[England]], [[United Kingdom]] | location = Near [[Hemsby]] in [[Norfolk]] | status = Operational | construction_began = | commissioned = December 1992 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = | operator = | ps_units_operational = 10 | ps_units_manu_model = Vestas: V27 | wind_hub_height = | wind_rotor_diameter = | wind_rated_speed = | wind_farm_type = | wind_site_elevation = | wind_site_usage = | wind_offshore_depth = | wind_offshore_distance = | ps_electrical_capacity = 2.25&nbsp;MW | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = https://web.archive.org/web/20070402205350/http://www.eon-uk.com/451.aspx }}
'''Blood Hill''' is a wind farm near [[Hemsby]] in [[Norfolk]], [[England]]. It is the smallest windfarm owned by [[E.ON]]; taking up 3 hectares.<ref>[http://www.eon-uk.com/451.aspx E.ON UK - Blood Hill<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070402205350/http://www.eon-uk.com/451.aspx |date=April 2, 2007 }}</ref> It has a [[nameplate capacity]] of 2.25[[Megawatt|MW]] which is enough to power 1000 homes at peak. There are 10 [[Vestas]] V27-225&nbsp;kW<ref name="windpower database">{{Cite web |url=http://www.thewindpower.net/wind-farm-1415-blood-hill-vestas-v27-225.php |title=Blood Hill windfarm, United-Kingdom |accessdate=2009-07-04 |publisher=Windpower database }}</ref> turbines which are 30 metres tall and stand on top of Blood Hill. They are visible from the villages of Hemsby and [[Winterton-on-Sea]]. Blood Hill began operating in December 1992 and was one of the first windfarms in the United Kingdom.
In 2000 a much larger 65m 1.5MW [[Ecotricity]] turbine was built adjacent to the site.<ref>http://www.ecotricity.co.uk/wind-parks/</ref>
In 2015 a repowering of the site saw the original 10 turbines replaced with 2 two Turbowind T400 wind turbines.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://planning.great-yarmouth.gov.uk/OcellaWeb/planningDetails?reference=06/13/0093/F&from=planningSearch|title=Great Yarmouth Borough Council|website=planning.great-yarmouth.gov.uk|access-date=2017-01-20}}</ref>
