A '''carbon audit regime''' is a means of [[accounting]] for quantifiable [[Mitigation of global warming|greenhouse gas control]] efforts.  It establishes that the claimed reductions in emissions or enhancements of [[carbon dioxide sinks|carbon sinks]], has actually occurred and is stable.

The [[United Kingdom|UK]] is the only nation in the world that presently has such a regime.

